This paper focuses on early rumor detection on Twitter using neural models and extensive feature analysis. The primary focus is on social media analysis (cs.SOC) and natural language processing (cs.CL) to detect rumors and misinformation. The paper also discusses the use of information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques to identify relevant tweets and features. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cybersecurity (cs.CY) techniques to detect and prevent the spread of misinformation. Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning and data mining techniques, which are commonly found in the sub-category of social network analysis (cs.SI).
